<p>
  Every reading on a multimeter, clamp meter, insulation tester, or LCR meter traces back to one equation. If you truly understand Ohm's Law, you understand <em>what every electrical tester is actually doing</em> — and why each instrument exists.
</p>

<!-- ── WHAT IS OHM'S LAW ── -->
<h2 id="what-is">What Is Ohm's Law?</h2>

<p>
  Stated simply: <strong>the current through a conductor is directly proportional to the voltage across it, and inversely proportional to its resistance</strong>. It was established by German physicist Georg Simon Ohm in 1827 and became one of the bedrock laws of electrical engineering.
</p>

<!-- Hero formula card -->
<div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0D1B2A] to-[#1B3A5B] p-8 text-center shadow-xl border border-white/10">
  <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-[#E0252E] mb-4">The Core Equation</p>
  <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight mb-4" style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;">
    V = I × R
  </div>
  <div class="flex justify-center gap-8 mt-6">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#E0252E]">V</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] mt-1">Voltage<br/>(Volts)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-400">I</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] mt-1">Current<br/>(Amperes)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-400">R</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#94a3b8] mt-1">Resistance<br/>(Ohms)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── TRIANGLE ── -->
<h2 id="triangle">The OHM Triangle — Rearranging in Seconds</h2>

<p>
  Engineers use a visual triangle to rearrange Ohm's Law on the fly. Cover the quantity you want to find — the remaining two show the calculation.
</p>

<!-- Ohm's triangle infographic -->
<div class="my-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
  <div class="bg-[#0D1B2A] px-6 py-3">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-[#94a3b8]">Infographic — Ohm's Law Triangle</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center justify-center">
    <!-- Triangle SVG -->
    <svg viewBox="0 0 200 180" class="w-48 shrink-0" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <!-- Triangle body -->
      <polygon points="100,10 10,170 190,170" fill="#0D1B2A" stroke="#E0252E" stroke-width="2"/>
      <!-- Dividing line -->
      <line x1="10" y1="110" x2="190" y2="110" stroke="#E0252E" stroke-width="2"/>
      <!-- V label -->
      <text x="100" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="38" font-weight="900" fill="#E0252E" font-family="monospace">V</text>
      <!-- I label -->
      <text x="63" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="28" font-weight="900" fill="#60A5FA" font-family="monospace">I</text>
      <!-- × -->
      <text x="100" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" fill="#94a3b8" font-family="sans-serif">×</text>
      <!-- R label -->
      <text x="138" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="28" font-weight="900" fill="#34D399" font-family="monospace">R</text>
    </svg>

    <!-- Three formula cards -->
    <div class="flex-1 grid gap-3">
      {[
        { cover:'V', result:'V = I × R', desc:'Cover V — multiply current by resistance to find voltage.', color:'border-[#E0252E] bg-red-50 text-[#E0252E]' },
        { cover:'I', result:'I = V ÷ R', desc:'Cover I — divide voltage by resistance to find current.', color:'border-blue-400 bg-blue-50 text-blue-600' },
        { cover:'R', result:'R = V ÷ I', desc:'Cover R — divide voltage by current to find resistance.', color:'border-emerald-400 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700' },
      ].map(f => (
        <div class={`flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border-2 ${f.color}`}>
